%N A396007 Smallest fibbinary multiplier k such that k*A396006(n) is fibbinary.
%C A396007 A number is fibbinary (A003714) if its base 2 representation contains no two consecutive 1's.  The sequence A396006(n) gives the n'th number with a representation as the quotient of two fibbinary numbers A/B.  This sequence lists the associated B for each element of A396006.
%H A396007 J. V. F. Meleshko, <a href="http://hdl.handle.net/10012/18952">Automata and ratio sets</a>, Master's thesis, University of Waterloo, 2022.
